commit.message:
Add Contributor Covenant's code of conduct

Signed-off-by: Robbie Harwood <rharwood@redhat.com>

Fix bashisms in configure.ac

'==' is not supported in POSIX shells. = is equivalent for us, so let's
use that instead.

This led to breakage when using e.g. dash as the system shell (rather than Bash)
as it caused support for e.g. gssproxy to be misdetected and broken binaries
were produced.

Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/762823
Signed-off-by: Sam James <sam@gentoo.org>

Fix use-after-free in verto_reinitialize()

Linked-list deletion didn't actually happen, and we'd try to
reinitialize freed modules (that weren't reinitializable anyway).

Discovered by scan-build.

Signed-off-by: Robbie Harwood <rharwood@redhat.com>

Fix use-after-free in verto_free()

Instead of freeing all events, verto_free() would spin trying to free
the same one.

Discovered by scan-build.

Signed-off-by: Robbie Harwood <rharwood@redhat.com>

Remove tevent support since tevent is broken

See-also: https://bugzilla.samba.org/show_bug.cgi?id=12987
Resolves: #16
Signed-off-by: Robbie Harwood <rharwood@redhat.com>

Update project metadata

Signed-off-by: Robbie Harwood <rharwood@redhat.com>

[ci] Port to GitHub Actions

Migrate el7 builder to el8.  Works around a Travis problem wherein
docker inexplicably thought cwd was unwritable on Debian.

Re-order pkgconfig for expected dependencies

Certain versions of autotools seem to generate recursive pkgconfig
files such that exec_prefix is defined in terms of prefix, and libdir
is defined in terms of exec_prefix.  While all orderings are possible,
attempt to cope with this apparently common one.

Resolves: #25

Bump for 0.3.1 release

Signed-off-by: Robbie Harwood <rharwood@redhat.com>
Fix rare leak of DSO in module_load

[travis] Downgrade Fedora from rawhide to latest

Rawhide currently is having trouble with conflicts around gdbm.

Signed-off-by: Robbie Harwood <rharwood@redhat.com>

Turn off -Wcast-function-type

The glib event library forces all callbacks to the same type, even
when they have different arities.  Turn off the gcc warning for this
gross behavior.
Verify flags prior to adding them to CFLAGS, not after
Work around libev not being c89-compliant
Bump for 0.3.0 release

Enforce c89 across codebase

Update build flags and built flag checking, as well as removing an
errant c99-ism.

Replace int_asprintf() with string concatenation

Previous asprintf() implementation contained a call to va_copy(),
which isn't in c89.  All usages were for string concatenation.
[travis] Add builder for BUILTIN_MODULE
Remove INSTALL file
Restrict mutex debugging by assert() presence
Bump for 0.2.7 release
Tolerate more rawhide misbehaviors in CI

Add verto_cleanup() to free loaded_modules

Implements a new call, verto_cleanup() to be called after all contexts
have been freed before program exit. Also adds verto_cleanup() in the
test cases. This also ensures that filename is freed in do_load_file()
on error paths.

Signed-off-by: Alexander Scheel <ascheel@redhat.com>
[rharwood@redhat.com: use new mutex destruction, rewrite docs, fix function
declarations, and C99 style nits]

Explicitly require c99 support

This is not a new requirement: we already needed c99 support for certain
functions (e.g., va_copy()).  However, gcc doesn't error out if functions
introduced in newer versions of the C standard are accessed when the standard
is something older.

Update mutex usage to improve debugging

Guard failures with assert(), log error messages, and add a
mutex_destroy() function.

Fix memleak in libverto:vfree

verto_set_allocator(resize, hierarchical) has an unducumented
requirement on allocator function resize, that resize(ptr, 0) is
equivalent to free(ptr).

Some implementations of the default allocator realloc don't meet this
requirement. realloc(ptr, 0) may return a unique pointer that can be
successfully passed to free. This new pointer never gets freed and the
memory overhead leaks.

This fix replaces realloc(ptr, 0) with free(ptr) in vresize and
documents the allocator requirement.

[rharwood@redhat.com: Cleanup comments slightly]
Closes: #18
Enable (and fix) all warnings
Add a CI target for clang
Add Travis support
bump for 0.2.6 release
